		<exercise xml:id="x_realworld-ball">
			<title>A*R*C*S Throwing a Ball</title>
			<statement>
				<p>
					
				</p>
			<p>While lying on the ground, you throw a ball that flies through the air and lands on the ground 
				a known distance <m>d</m> away from you after a total time <m>T</m>.  
				Find the initial velocity with which you threw the ball.</p>
			</statement>
			<hint>
			<p>Part 1a from the <xref ref="fig_realworld"/> can be especially helpful in keeping track of all the 
				known and unknown quantities.</p>
			</hint>

			<answer>
				<p>
					Starting with the <m>x</m>-direction position equation:
					<me>
						v_{ix} = \frac{d}{T}
					</me>
					Then using the <m>y</m>-direction position equation:
					<me>
						v_{iy} = \frac{1}{2}gT^2
					</me>
					And putting it all together:
					<me>
						\vec{v}_{i} = \frac{d}{T}\hat{x} + \frac{1}{2}gT^2\hat{y}
					</me>
					
					
				</p>


